  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study is designed to test two hypotheses:

        1. The PADnet+ testing system produces clinically equivalent results as the Parks Flo-Lab
           testing system in a group of patients referred for evaluation of PAD of the limbs when
           performed by a Registered Vascular Technologist (RVT).

        2. The PADnet+ testing system produces clinically equivalent results when the testing is
           repeated on the above patients and performed by staff specifically trained on the use of
           the PADnet+ system but are not vascular technologists nor hold the RVT certification.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
